The paper discusses the correlation between culture and e-commerce website design, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper also touches upon information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects of e-commerce website design. The paper also discusses the importance of local businesses in the global e-commerce marketplace, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
